By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Governor
Kayode Fayemi of Ekiti on Thursday stepped down as governor for
7-year-old Daniel Adaramodu of African Grammar School to be governor of Ekiti
State for the day. Fayemi may have to engage
in activities other than being governor throughout the day as Daniel performs
his duty as governor. Details later…